It was always great to see interesting projects that seemed like they were fueled by pure intrigue or curiosity. Lately its all been sponsored content, and doesnt feel whimsical and fun any more. It just feels like a long commercial, and I get plenty of commercials through the day just by being alive and coherent. Also, i dont like commercials at all. I dont know how many more commercials i can stick around for, dude. It's a bit tiresome at this point.

Educational as always. That radius jig is nice and simple. I'll have to remember that when I'm building my own turbojet cart.
One thing I did learn while making steel and aluminum cylinders, though, is if you brake the edge just a bit it'll roll right out to the edge without the flat tail, so less material waste.
